adjectives.description: unoriginal (comparative more unoriginal, superlative most unoriginal)

examples: Redundancies are as unoriginal as Insipidities, and the Spirit of an Author may be as much overwhelmed in Exuberance on the one Hand, as it evaporates in Frigidity on the other.

entries.meaning: (rare) Not being the first or earliest version of something, not original.
examples: [This tale] occurs in an MS. of the fifteenth century in an obviously unoriginal form which shows that the story-teller did not appreciate the significance of many features in the folk-tale he was retelling  […]

entries.meaning: A person or work that does not exhibit originality.
examples: Ahmad (1969) studied the personality differences among middle school girls identified as originals and unoriginals on the Minnesota's test of creative thinking.
